==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hunker
<hw>Hun"ker</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Originally, a nickname
for a member of the conservative section of the Democratic party in New
York; hence, one opposed to progress in general; a fogy.</def>
<mark>[Political Cant, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hunker down</ent>⟦br⟧
